Let’s get our sh*t together — together.

After making the bold move to move countries and quit my job to “live life on my own terms,” I thought I’d be thriving.

But honestly? I’ve lost my routine, my drive — and maybe even a little bit of me.

The 20s confusion is real.

Now, It’s time to reset — mentally, emotionally, physically. Time to show up for YOU. To trying new things, building better habits, and actually going after your dreams.

So I’m starting a new series: “Get Your Sh*t Together” — for anyone craving more discipline, more balance, and a more fulfilling life.

Let’s do this. Together🤍.

latestPosts.caption:
almost been a year since I moved back to India after living in london for 3 years. 

visiting london as a “tourist” was bittersweet. I was very anxious at first and didn’t want to go. but once I was there, it was just too hard to leave again. 

I hadn’t been feeling my best self since a while. the motivation, the hustle, the excitement around my career — all of it had taken a backseat. but those 6 days in london were a blessing in disguise, almost like it was meant to be — to reconnect with the version of me that believed, that dreamed, that built a life from scratch in a foreign country. 

now, I’m slowly finding that spark again. taking it one day at a time — for the girl who worked so hard to get me here. 

this is your sign to keep going to make your past self feel proud and future self secure🤍.
.
.
